\"Like P7, this is convincing through the aspartate stage and well anchored in Patel-style chemistry. It fails mainly at the final amidation step, which the literature specifically identifies as unsolved. Good as a precursor pathway, not yet as a validated asparagine pathway.\",\n      \"approved\": false,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_015\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Present aspartate as the validated product and asparagine amidation as a research gap.\",\n        \"Consider coupling amidation claims to rapid trapping into peptides if the route is preserved.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P9\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_001\": 0.82,\n        \"rxn_014\": 0.8,\n        \"rxn_013\": 0.91\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.84,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.88,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.83,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.9,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.87,\n      \"feedback\": \"This route is a reasonable hybrid path: hydrothermal pyruvate to alanine is plausible, and alanine plus formamide under contact glow discharge has direct literature support from Munegumi. The main concern is that the final discharge chemistry is not really 'biochemical' but a distinct energy-driven geophysical environment. Still, as a target-achieving route it is credible.\",\n      \"approved\": true,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Reclassify the final step as discharge/plasma surface-atmosphere chemistry rather than biochemical.\",\n        \"Clarify whether alanine concentration and formamide-rich conditions are realistic in the proposed setting.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P10\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_011\": 0.92,\n        \"rxn_017\": 0.63\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.76,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.88,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.81,\n      \"target_achieveme